Justice Muhammad Lawu Lawan of the Yobe State High Court, on Monday, sentenced the auditor general for Local Government, Yobe State, Alhaji Idris Yahaya to five years imprisonment.  Yahaya, who is standing trial over alleged misappropriation was found guilty and convicted by Justice Muhammad Lawu Lawan of the Yobe State High Court on a one-count charge of criminal misappropriation to the tune of N19, 900million. According to the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, Yahaya received funds from the Office of the Auditor General for Local Government and Emirate Affairs, Yobe State for the purchase of an official vehicle, a 2015 Toyota Corolla and diverted part of the money to his personal use.  The one-count charge reads: ”That you, Yahaya Lawal Idris, being the Auditor General for Local Government, Yobe State, between the 20th to 21st day of May, 2017 at Damaturu, Yobe State within the jurisdiction of this Honourable Court, received the sum of N19,900,000.00 via your personal account number 1001480930 with account name Alhaji Yahaya Idris domiciled in United Bank for Africa Plc (UBA) from the Local Government Audit Account Number 5030030060 domiciled in Fidelity Bank Plc for the purchase of a brand new Toyota Corolla 2015 Model, did dishonestly misappropriated the gross sum of N10,100,000.00 (Ten Million, One Hundred Thousand Naira) only.” The Nation gathered he was first arraigned on Wednesday, November 9, 2022 and pleaded not guilty to the charges, setting the stage for his full trial. In the course of the trial, counsel for the EFCC, Mukhtar Ali Ahmed called four witnesses and tendered documents that were admitted in evidence.  Delivering judgment on Monday, Justice Lawan held the prosecution has proved the case against the defendant and convicted him as charged.  He consequently sentenced him to five-year imprisonment with an option of fine.  The Judge further directed the convict to pay N10m in restitution to Yobe State Government through the EFCC or serve additional two years in prison.